Women of reproductive age (aged 15-49 years) who have their need for family planning satisfied with modern methods (%)
Comments: The global indicator represents all women of reproductive age. This survey estimate represents women who are married or in a union. Unmet need data pertain to fecund married women who were not currently using contraception and who wanted no more births, wanted to postpone the next birth for at least two years or were undecided about whether to have another birth or the timing of that birth. Sri Lanka 2000 Demographic and Health Survey (national)
